Therefore no number which is greater than CF will measure the
             numbers AB , CD ; 
               therefore CF is the greatest common measure of AB , CD .

But it measures C also; therefore E
             measures A , B , C ;
             therefore E is a common measure of A , B , C .

Therefore no number which is greater than E will measure the
             numbers A , B , C ;
             therefore E is the greatest common measure of A , B , C . Q. E. D.

Let A , B be numbers prime to one another;
             I say that A , B are the least of those
             which have the same ratio with them.
